Go to the extension section on the VS code to install "Remote- ssh"
You will see a "><" at the left bottom of the screen, click on it 
Search for Open SSH Configuration file 
Click on the path from your local system
Create a hostfile (look below) 
Host Jenkins
    HostName 30.133.14.12
    User ec2-user
    IdentityFile ~/Downloads/Class29.pem.pem
You will see a "><" at the left bottom of the screen, click on it 
Click on "connent to Host"
Select the host and this will automatically SSH into the sever
On the bottom which is the terminal you can access the server e.g cd into file or make a directory
if you want to write into the file you need the "editor" to switch use the the command "code ."
